About the job
About XO Sports
XO Sports is building a next-gen B2C mobile platform for the online sports market, starting with the NBA and expanding into AFL, NRL, and NFL over the next 12 months. Our platform is powered by Azure cloud, leveraging a broad range of data services including Data Factory, Databricks, ADLS Gen2 and github to enabling us to ingest, transform data model for ML training. These insights can then be published real-time insights to fans and punters.

Role Summary
We’re looking for a hands-on Data Scientist to join our growing backend team. You’ll be responsible for designing, training, and deploying the machine learning models that power our predictive analytics and in-app insights. This is a unique opportunity to own the end-to-end modeling lifecycle—from feature engineering in Databricks to real-time model deployment—helping shape the future of sports analytics.

What You’ll Be Doing
Model Development: Design and train predictive models (e.g., player performance, win probabilities, betting lines) using Python and Spark.
Feature Engineering: Collaborate with data engineers to develop and maintain high-signal features within a Delta Lake medallion architecture.
Statistical Analysis: Perform deep-dive analysis on raw NBA and multi-sport datasets to identify trends, biases, and opportunities for new model iterations.
MLOps & Deployment: Use Databricks and Azure Machine Learning to manage the model lifecycle, ensuring low-latency inference for real-time fan insights.
Validation & Tuning: Ensure model robustness through rigorous backtesting, cross-validation, and monitoring of model drift.
Collaboration: Work closely with backend developers to integrate model outputs into the mobile app via Azure Function Apps and CosmosDB.
Version Control: Use GitHub for reproducible research and collaborate in an Agile environment using Jira.

What You Bring
You’re a curious problem-solver who excels at turning messy sports data into actionable predictions. You write clean, production-ready Python and understand the mathematical foundations behind the models you build.

Must-haves:
Statistical Programming: Strong Python skills, specifically with the PyData stack (pandas, scikit-learn, NumPy) and Spark/PySpark for large-scale data.
Databricks Expertise: Experience building models within the Databricks ecosystem, utilizing Delta Tables and MLflow for experiment tracking.
Predictive Modeling: Proven experience in supervised and unsupervised learning, including regression, classification, and time-series forecasting.
Feature Design: Ability to conceptualize and engineer complex features from raw, unstructured (JSONL) sports data.
Evaluation Rigor: Strong understanding of model evaluation metrics and the ability to conduct rigorous offline and online testing.
Cloud Fluency: Familiarity with the Azure ecosystem (ADLSv2, Azure ML, or Databricks) for data access and model scaling.

Nice-to-haves:
Sports Domain Knowledge: A passion for sports (NBA, AFL, NRL, NFL) and a deep understanding of advanced sports metrics.
Probabilistic Modeling: Experience with Bayesian stats or Monte Carlo simulations for sports betting or gaming contexts.
Deployment Experience: Experience with containerization or API integration for real-time model serving.

