About the job
About Us:
 Verian is a world leading, purpose-led and independent research, evidence, evaluation, and communications agency, providing services to government and the public realm. With offices across the globe, our specialist consultants and researchers are supported by our unique global data ecosystem. We provide gold standard data on the economy and society to decision makers.

We combine expertise in human understanding with advanced technologies and data science, connecting governments with citizens across the world. We support the rapid development of policy thinking in moments of urgency. We implement policies on the ground for multi-laterals. We build communications to reach diverse and complex audiences.

We are Verian. Powering decisions that shape the world. 
 
Purpose of the role: 

The primary responsibility of this role is Independently leading small / mid-size projects, including client management, design of all materials, reporting and presentation. Leading larger projects under supervision / with support of senior staff, including all facets of the project. Developing and maintaining client relationships and identifying opportunities for growth in the business 
 Key responsibilities: 
 Winning work 
Leads medium complexity proposals with continuing support from senior staff in the development of highly complex proposals. 
Able to design an appropriate methodology to meet clients’ objectives and budget and understands the broader issues impacting project scope and feasibility. 
 Leading projects 
Manages client relationship throughout the project, leading discussions on approach, progress and client impact. 
Able to independently develop all materials required for data collection and brief the project team to ensure everyone understands the client’s needs and their role in the project. 
Manages any issues through the project finding solutions and, where necessary, advising senior staff of any potential impacts on the business. 
Independently develops questionnaire and discussion guides. 
 Analysis and Reporting 
Can independently prepare a full report for medium complexity projects and provide a full draft for more highly complex projects, including development of the ‘story’ report, implications and conclusions that address the client’s objectives. 
Able to create and deliver a concise and engaging presentation demonstrating insight against client objectives 
 Managing client relationships 
Builds strong client relationships that go beyond the delivery of the project in isolation. Understands the client’s world and what is impacting them, and how this may impact our work together. 
Able to identify growth opportunities and have proactive conversations with clients about them. 
  Staff Development 
Mentor and manage junior staff providing regular feedback on performance, create a development plan, meet regularly to assess performance against development goals and KPIs. 
  Role capabilities: 
Understand both qualitative and quantitative methods and how to utilise them appropriately to design a research program to meet client needs and budget 
5 - 7 years’ experience in the research and consulting industry 
Be able to draw conclusions from our evidence that address our client’s objectives 
Articulate insights (both in writing and in person / presentation) to provide clients with outcomes that meet or exceed expectations 
Present confidently to both internal and external audiences 


Why Join Us:

The chance to work on high-impact, meaningful projects that drive real-world change
A competitive salary and benefits package
Learning and development opportunities to help you grow professionally
A collaborative, purpose-led team that supports diversity and inclusivity
Up to 5 weeks of annual leave per year
Work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks within any 12-month period


